<subSubSection id="DEDAA918650EA2F5AEA3890E2FBC3414" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="triangularia species group">
<paragraph id="C7C02EF40BD43DE72A7726BD5D8D7EDC" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
<taxonomicName id="E9D6D81DE259BADD04AB1EB4807B6EE4" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona triangularia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularia">
<emphasis id="39E22A6A758BD076B2096C9C91AD3A86" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona triangularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A9622D334C827CD4B7D5C211C016B9FB" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
Based on 
<bibRefCitation id="E029441F00E0055D824D2B51F93857E3" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" author="Wilkinson, C" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Zoological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="407 - 517" refId="B26" refString="Wilkinson, C, 1968. A Taxonomic revision of the genus Ditrigona (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae: Drepaninae). Transactions of the Zoological Society of London 31 (4): 407 - 517, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" title="A Taxonomic revision of the genus Ditrigona (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae: Drepaninae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" volume="31" year="1968">Wilkinson (1968)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="FC6E808B8C7F5B3AEAA3F1AEFE6791BA" author="Jiang, S" journalOrPublisher="Entomotaxonomia" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="81 - 88" refId="B12" refString="Jiang, S, Han, HX, 2019. A new species of Ditrigona Moore (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae) in China, with a checklist to the triangularia -group. Entomotaxonomia 41 (2): 81 - 88" title="A new species of Ditrigona Moore (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae) in China, with a checklist to the triangularia - group." volume="41" year="2019">Jiang and Han (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<taxonomicName id="0E379495B65F7EF0AE747BF31CB486F5" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona triangularia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularia">
<emphasis id="5B7CC8A14CDE0E8F2A44F41C161B6322" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona triangularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group contains ten species, in which 
<taxonomicName id="CB34040A5A0E07C78C8A38E3AAC667DC" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona triangularia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularia">
<emphasis id="D257363E25D85D9C238162F3D7643232" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona triangularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Moore), 
<taxonomicName id="E4F27173506CBBF2E5A169DE4BDA684C" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona regularis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="regularis">
<emphasis id="9314674F5F9CC9083DBA98A56601F1A6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona regularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Warren, 
<taxonomicName id="495CCA48332815D9D8DBE0029ACFE4F9" authorityName="Chu &amp; Wang" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona uniuncusa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uniuncusa">
<emphasis id="1E9444C62312C9FB28EB8577F5E762D8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona uniuncusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chu &amp; Wang, and 
<taxonomicName id="484575BE44A56CF040A6075D6FD68C80" authorityName="Jiang &amp; Han" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona tenuiata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuiata">
<emphasis id="A5E5290CFE83BA628F5A7AB2A084AEE1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona tenuiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jiang &amp; Han bear elongate posterior projections of the hind wings (tail process); the other six species, 
<taxonomicName id="BCF833F230DB21F0A36C4EB28D75D546" authorityName="Wilkinson" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona titana" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="titana">
<emphasis id="1B91EBF53441DBEAAA02CB2BBB83A330" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona titana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wilkinson, 
<taxonomicName id="68CCDA15E73C701165473C48F6876850" baseAuthorityName="Oberthuer" baseAuthorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona pomenaria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pomenaria">
<emphasis id="55EF2BA0024363F8F60A78CEB88C4329" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona pomenaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="6823D57224A7C864AEF6D8AEC131F13F" originalValue="Oberthür">Oberthuer</normalizedToken>
), 
<taxonomicName id="FEB16B910D936346BAAFAFAE6D40011E" authorityName="Wilkinson" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona typhodes" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="typhodes">
<emphasis id="C276526962CB0CA58B366F280E062EBA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona typhodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wilkinson, 
<taxonomicName id="5FC910388BE87373DC31D08B9B304284" baseAuthorityName="Oberthuer" baseAuthorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona polyobotaria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polyobotaria">
<emphasis id="2A0FD9CEC606AAB49355CAF2A8DB5DF9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona polyobotaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="E21CF37597F7794CA59B69DB4352AE6A" originalValue="Oberthür">Oberthuer</normalizedToken>
), 
<taxonomicName id="88F5676DB16044ABFB1E2A6662410085" authorityName="Wilkinson" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona sciara" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sciara">
<emphasis id="06694A5C44AF489362B9AE99673AB1BA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona sciara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wilkinson, and 
<taxonomicName id="B168B84D72210C687740756ED6BC7F2E" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona fasciata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis id="E8457896CBB1464DB1A723C91C55D92C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hampson) lack the tail process. The first nine species are recorded in China, and three new species (
<taxonomicName id="1A3B7ED73E331BC5D5858C44624C266B" family="Drepanidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. sinespina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="sinespina">
<emphasis id="6ED17EE1C0C7FE8976C589F69D280C72" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">D. sinespina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0EFDD61BF1620EB8F7BB0ECB8FFC2AE8" family="Drepanidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. parva" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="parva">
<emphasis id="4FF0F470A0227085E29311EA56391C3E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">D. parva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="97443F605C1F204E153831E9013EABE6" family="Drepanidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. concava" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="concava">
<emphasis id="F195E12913066F0AFBD6C648EA585668" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">D. concava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) with the tail process are described in this work.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="140FEE92FF72D46E5D10A11C5A65BF8C" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
The species with a tail process on the hind wing have quite distinct wing patterns: the hind wing has the postmedial and submarginal lines approaching each other near the anal angle, and bears a small black patch at the upper angle of the tail. The species lacking a tail process resemble some species of the 
<emphasis id="5943464EE56623E1F4953C580BE7C618" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">mytylata</emphasis>
species group, in that they have transverse lines which often resemble a narrow band. In the male genitalia, the valva is characterized by having a small flap-like extension. The species with a tail process can also be distinguished by the large rounded socii and the stout aedeagus bearing a brush-like cornutus. In the species lacking a tail process, the aedeagus is narrow, straight or bent, and the cornutus is a simple process or absent. The eighth sternite is small, shallowly concave or protruding in species with a tail process, and the eighth tergite almost unmodified. Both eighth tergite and sternite often possess octavals in the species lacking a tail process. In the female genitalia, the ostium bursae is usually large, and the ductus bursae is often indiscernible, but wide and obvious in 
<taxonomicName id="73544B32349FF5BA21DE77548A3C88A0" family="Drepanidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. typhodes" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="typhodes">
<emphasis id="95BA0792D2C811B884F7DD1875E3318F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">D. typhodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The corpus bursae bears a small accessory sac in species with a tail process. (modified from Wilkinson, 1968)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9A408DCFB070339333E6D2399F4B6B50" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
16 DAN barcoding sequences were obtained for 
<taxonomicName id="15810A2E3934BDA69BB83B9755986F96" family="Drepanidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. regularis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="regularis">
<emphasis id="130E04539B81AF9FA410D59B944B614F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">D. regularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="23D0A1C5ACCD359907CD14329C93FDE6" family="Drepanidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. triangularia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="triangularia">
<emphasis id="A863C0B4EA648A2CA1F3BF72AAFD23AF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">D. triangularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DD4679ADD4B687993B0ACB4045AB103A" family="Drepanidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. tenuiata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="tenuiata">
<emphasis id="63519AD135E165A89B445955CAD2C820" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">D. tenuiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
